 Sure, I can help you create an XML file for your robotic mission plan based on the instructions you provided. Here's a sample XML file that represents your mission plan:
```php
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<mission>
  <task name="Take picture of first tree">
    <subtask name="Take picture of first tree"/>
    <subtask name="Measure co2 level in first tree"/>
    <if condition="co2_level is low">
      <subtask name="Take co2 sample in first tree"/>
      <if condition="co2_sample is low">
        <subtask name="Confirm co2 sample in first tree"/>
        <subtask name="Drive to next tree and take co2 sample"/>
      </if>
    </if>
  </task>
  <task name="Measure another tree">
    <subtask name="Take picture of second tree"/>
    <if condition="co2_level is low">
      <subtask name="Take co2 sample in second tree"/>
      <if condition="co2_sample is low">
        <subtask name="Confirm co2 sample in second tree"/>
        <subtask name="Drive to next tree and take co2 sample"/>
      </if>
    </if>
  </task>
  <end/>
</mission>
```
This XML file represents a mission plan with two tasks: "Take picture of first tree" and "Measure another tree". Each task has one or more subtasks that represent the specific actions to be performed. The `<if>` element is used to conditionally execute certain subtasks based on the outcome of previous ones.

In this case, the mission plan starts by taking a picture of the first tree and measuring its co2 level. If the co2 level is low, it takes a co2 sample to confirm. If the co2 level is still low, it drives to another tree and takes another co2 sample. The same process is repeated for the second tree. Finally, the mission ends.

I hope this helps you get started with creating your XML file for your robotic mission plan! 